<text id="04-procedure" title="Poetry Project Setup — Procedure" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="700" depth="medium">
  <summary>Step-by-step procedure for applying python-poetry-setup.</summary>

    <section title="Step 1: poetry init">
      <p>Input: Empty dir</p>
      <p>Action: Run poetry init; accept PEP 621 layout.</p>
      <p>Output: pyproject with [project].</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 2: Add dependencies">
      <p>Input: [project] open</p>
      <p>Action: poetry add httpx pydantic.</p>
      <p>Output: Runtime deps.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 3: Add dev group">
      <p>Input: Runtime added</p>
      <p>Action: poetry add --group dev pytest ruff mypy.</p>
      <p>Output: Dev group separate.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 4: Lock">
      <p>Input: Deps added</p>
      <p>Action: poetry lock; commit poetry.lock.</p>
      <p>Output: Reproducible install.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 5: Wire pre-commit">
      <p>Input: Tools installed</p>
      <p>Action: poetry run pre-commit install.</p>
      <p>Output: Local gate.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 6: Publish (if library)">
      <p>Input: Wheel builds</p>
      <p>Action: poetry build &amp;&amp; poetry publish.</p>
      <p>Output: Released to PyPI.</p>
    </section>
</text>
